-- allium: 3
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium
--
-- Scope: the slot state machine and the chunked-prefill admission
-- contracts that compose a single per-tick batch from decode +
-- prefill contributions. Under Tier 4 (chunked-prefill admission,
-- Sarathi-Serve), a single Batch may contain BOTH decode tokens
-- (from PROCESSING slots) and prefill chunks (from one or more
-- LOAD_PROMPT slots), subject to a token-budget K and a
-- decode-first admission ordering.
--
-- Why this spec exists: PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF T3.8 (closed FAIL
-- 2026-05-22) measured M2 prefill-stall fraction at 77.9% — the
-- per-stream dispatch unification from Tier 3 closed Bug C
-- structurally (via the 4D KV layout, `unified_stream_dispatch`),
-- but throughput at NP=8 is locked away by prefill stalls, not
-- dispatch packing. Tier 4 admits prefill chunks into the same
-- llama_decode ubatch as running decodes — the lever vLLM uses
-- to reach 154.77 t/s on the same hardware. This spec pins the
-- admission contracts so they cannot quietly regress.
--
-- @guidance
--     -- Bug C closure is DELEGATED to specs/dispatch/
--     -- unified_stream_dispatch.allium. The Tier 3 per-stream
--     -- 4D KV layout (ne[3] = n_stream) and uniform mul_mat
--     -- shape per tick are what make mixed prefill+decode
--     -- batches safe: every ubatch sees a single [d, n_total]
--     -- mul_mat call regardless of which slots contribute
--     -- tokens. The pre-Tier-3 scheduler invariants
--     -- (MixedBatchProhibition, AtMostOnePrefillSlotPerBatch,
--     -- DecodeHoldImpliedByPendingPrefill) were defence-in-depth
--     -- that pre-dated the structural closure; under Tier 4
--     -- they are removed. The empirical Bug-C-absence test
--     -- (scripts/r5-probe-c4.sh) remains the binding gate.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the server scheduler objects
--     (Slot, Tick, Batch, BatchToken).
--   - Enumerations for slot_state (matching slot_state in
--     server-context.h:14) and slot_command (server-context.h:21).
--   - Contracts for the chunked-prefill admission policy:
--     TokenBudgetPerUbatch, DecodePriorityAdmission,
--     ChunkedPrefillAdmission, PrefillCarryProgressesMonotonically.
--   - SlotLifecycle covering the existing IDLE↔PROCESSING
--     transitions plus the implicit carry-across-ticks state
--     (a Slot stays at command=load_prompt while
--     n_past_prompt < n_prompt_tokens).
--   - System-wide BatchCompositionInvariant redefined as the
--     conjunction of the admission contracts (so downstream
--     specs that already cross-reference the name continue to
--     bind on the new semantics).
--   - Open questions naming the choices the implementation
--     deferred (Sarathi-Serve K-budget tuning, per-stream
--     scheduling under heterogeneous slot priorities).
--
-- Excludes:
--   - The DFlash draft graph and the per-ubatch MTP-KV hook;
--     those are covered by mtp_fused_draft.allium and
--     mtp_ubatch_hook.allium. The contracts there describe what
--     ONE draft round / ubatch produces given the batch shape
--     this spec governs.
--   - The KV cache layout itself (per-stream cells, slot↔cells
--     mapping). Owned by specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium.
--   - The numerical bound between NP=1 and NP>1 slot output.
--     Owned by the perf-determinism harness
--     (scripts/verify-production-determinism.sh) and
--     specs/deltanet/*.
--   - The qnext_analyze_seq_pattern engine routing inside
--     llama_decode. Owned by qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium.
--     That spec governs what the engine does given a batch;
--     THIS spec governs which batches the server may assemble.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — server scheduler objects
-- ============================================================

-- A server_slot, the per-session worker the HTTP layer assigns
-- arriving requests to. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:37-232. The
-- n_past_prompt field at line 60 advances by the number of
-- prefill tokens admitted in each Tick; the slot stays at
-- command=load_prompt across Ticks until n_past_prompt reaches
-- n_prompt_tokens, at which point ProcessingOnPrefillComplete in
-- SlotLifecycle fires.
external entity Slot {
    id: Integer
    state: SlotState
    command: SlotCommand
    released: Boolean
    n_prompt_tokens: Integer
    n_prompt_tokens_processed: Integer
    n_past_prompt: Integer
}

-- One update_slots() cycle (server-context.cpp:5078-5173). Each
-- Tick produces at most one llama_batch and at most one
-- llama_decode call. Under Tier 4 the admission loop in
-- batch_pending_prompt (rewritten by T4.4) assembles the Batch
-- by first admitting decode tokens from PROCESSING slots, then
-- admitting prefill chunks from LOAD_PROMPT slots
-- round-robin, both subject to a per-Tick token budget K.
external entity Tick {
    index: Integer
}

-- The llama_batch assembled in one Tick. May be empty, pure-
-- prefill, pure-decode, or — under Tier 4 — a mix of decode
-- tokens (one per active PROCESSING slot) and prefill chunks
-- (from one or more LOAD_PROMPT slots).
external entity Batch {
    tick: Tick
    n_tokens: Integer
}

-- One token in a Batch. is_prefill is true when the token was
-- contributed by the admission loop's prefill phase (a slot in
-- IDLE+LOAD_PROMPT). is_decode is true when contributed by the
-- decode phase (a slot in PROCESSING). Mutually exclusive
-- per-token (PerTokenFlagExclusivity below).
external entity BatchToken {
    batch: Batch
    slot: Slot
    is_prefill: Boolean
    is_decode: Boolean
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- Mirrors slot_state in ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:14-17.
enum SlotState { idle | processing }

-- Mirrors slot_command in ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:21-25.
enum SlotCommand { none | load_prompt | release }

-- ============================================================
-- Config
-- ============================================================

config {
    -- Maximum parallel slots the server may run. Mirrors
    -- --parallel N at start time, n_seq_max in cparams. The
    -- contracts hold for any value in [1, max_parallel_slots].
    max_parallel_slots: Integer = 8

    -- Per-Tick token budget K. The admission loop will not
    -- assemble a Batch with more than K tokens. Wired to the
    -- --prefill-chunk-budget CLI (T4.5); defaults to
    -- n_ubatch (cparams.n_ubatch) which collapses Tier 4 to
    -- legacy behaviour at the largest Sarathi K. Range
    -- [1, n_ubatch]; K = 0 is rejected at CLI parse.
    prefill_chunk_budget: Integer = 512
}

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- TokenBudgetPerUbatch — the Sarathi-Serve admission cap. Every
-- Batch this spec governs has at most K tokens, where K is the
-- per-server prefill_chunk_budget config. The admission loop
-- (server-context.cpp:batch_pending_prompt post-T4.4) consumes
-- the budget in two phases (decode then prefill); the cap is
-- the bound that gives chunked prefill its name.
contract TokenBudgetPerUbatch {
    invoke: (slots: Set<Slot>, tick: Tick, k: Integer) -> Batch

    @invariant BatchSizeBoundedByK
        -- For any Tick t and the Batch produced from it,
        -- BatchTokensOf(batch).count <= k. The bound binds
        -- regardless of how many slots are PROCESSING or
        -- LOAD_PROMPT.

    @invariant KMatchesConfig
        -- The k parameter to invoke equals the server's
        -- prefill_chunk_budget at the start of the Tick. K does
        -- not vary intra-Tick.

    @invariant KAtLeastOne
        -- k >= 1 at all times. The CLI rejects K = 0; the
        -- contract has no edge case to handle for an empty
        -- budget.

    @guidance
        -- K is a latency knob: smaller K bounds time-between-
        -- tokens (TBT) for active decoding slots by limiting
        -- the prefill work per Tick. Production policy for K
        -- is out of scope for this spec — only the contract
        -- the policy must respect.
}

-- DecodePriorityAdmission — decodes are admitted before
-- prefill chunks in any Tick that contains both. The admission
-- loop (server-context.cpp post-T4.4) iterates PROCESSING slots
-- first, adds one decode token per slot (consuming budget),
-- then iterates LOAD_PROMPT slots round-robin filling the
-- remainder.
contract DecodePriorityAdmission {
    invoke: (slots: Set<Slot>, tick: Tick, k: Integer) -> Batch

    @invariant EveryProcessingSlotAdmittedIfBudgetSuffices
        -- For any Tick where the count of PROCESSING slots is
        -- at most k, every PROCESSING slot contributes exactly
        -- one BatchToken with is_decode = true to the Tick's
        -- Batch. Prefill admission consumes only the residual
        -- budget after decode.

    @invariant DecodeAdmittedBeforePrefillTokens
        -- If a Batch contains any BatchToken with
        -- is_prefill = true, then every PROCESSING slot whose
        -- decode token would have been admitted under the
        -- legacy decode-only path is also present as an
        -- is_decode token in the same Batch. Prefill chunks
        -- never bump decode tokens out of a Tick when budget
        -- is available.

    @invariant DecodeNeverHeldByPrefill
        -- The Tier 3 / pre-Tier-4 DecodeHoldGate
        -- (server-context.cpp:3196-3206) is gone: a Slot in
        -- (idle, load_prompt) does NOT cause PROCESSING slots
        -- to stall. The whole point of Tier 4 is to remove
        -- this stall.

    @guidance
        -- Decode-first matches Sarathi-Serve §3.2 and the
        -- vLLM continuous-batching scheduler. The intuition:
        -- decodes are short and latency-sensitive, prefill is
        -- bulky and amortises over chunks; admitting decode
        -- first bounds TBT under any prefill load.
}

-- ChunkedPrefillAdmission — when a LOAD_PROMPT slot's remaining
-- prefill exceeds the residual budget for prefill (after decode
-- admission), the unfit tail carries to the next Tick. The slot
-- stays in command=load_prompt; n_past_prompt advances by the
-- admitted count only.
contract ChunkedPrefillAdmission {
    invoke: (slot: Slot, tick: Tick, prefill_budget_residual: Integer) -> Slot

    @invariant AdmittedCountBoundedByResidual
        -- For a LOAD_PROMPT slot in a Tick, the number of
        -- prefill tokens admitted is
        -- min(prefill_budget_residual,
        --     slot.n_prompt_tokens - slot.n_past_prompt). At
        -- most that many BatchTokens with is_prefill = true,
        -- batch.slot = this slot are produced.

    @invariant SlotPersistsInLoadPromptUntilDone
        -- If after the Tick's admission
        -- slot.n_past_prompt < slot.n_prompt_tokens, the Slot
        -- remains at (idle, load_prompt). It is eligible for
        -- continued admission in subsequent Ticks via the
        -- round-robin LOAD_PROMPT iteration.

    @invariant RoundRobinFairness
        -- When multiple LOAD_PROMPT slots compete for the
        -- residual prefill budget in a Tick, the admission
        -- loop visits them in slot.id order. Each round of
        -- the round-robin admits at most one chunk per slot
        -- before re-visiting. The contract does NOT mandate
        -- equal per-slot admission per Tick; only that no
        -- LOAD_PROMPT slot is starved while another's chunks
        -- are still being added.

    @guidance
        -- Carry across Ticks is implicit in the existing slot
        -- state: n_past_prompt advances by the admitted count
        -- per Tick (the existing increment at
        -- server-context.cpp:3949 already does this). T4
        -- introduces no new slot field; only the admission
        -- loop's policy changes.
}

-- PrefillCarryProgressesMonotonically — a liveness contract
-- ensuring no LOAD_PROMPT slot is permanently stalled. Across
-- any non-empty sequence of Ticks, a LOAD_PROMPT slot's
-- n_past_prompt is non-decreasing, and reaches n_prompt_tokens
-- in finitely many Ticks (transitioning to PROCESSING via
-- SlotLifecycle.ProcessingOnPrefillComplete).
contract PrefillCarryProgressesMonotonically {
    invoke: (slot: Slot, ticks: List<Tick>) -> Slot

    @invariant MonotonicNPastPromptAcrossTicks
        -- For a Slot at (idle, load_prompt) across any
        -- consecutive pair of Ticks (t_i, t_{i+1}),
        -- slot.n_past_prompt[t_{i+1}] >=
        -- slot.n_past_prompt[t_i]. The slot never loses
        -- prefill progress.

    @invariant CompletesInFiniteTicks
        -- Provided the server continues to issue Ticks and
        -- the per-tick token budget K >= 1, any LOAD_PROMPT
        -- slot reaches n_past_prompt = n_prompt_tokens in at
        -- most ceiling(n_prompt_tokens / 1) = n_prompt_tokens
        -- Ticks (worst case: one prefill token per Tick when
        -- competing slots saturate budget). The bound is
        -- pessimistic; typical K admits dozens of chunks per
        -- Tick.

    @guidance
        -- The contract excludes "stalled forever" pathologies
        -- but does NOT bound TBT for any particular slot. SLO
        -- shaping (e.g., "prefill must complete within 10
        -- Ticks") is policy and lives outside this spec.
}

-- The lifecycle a Slot moves through across Ticks. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:534-538 (the
-- is_idle / is_available predicates), 578-582 (release path),
-- 1714 (LOAD_PROMPT assignment from incoming task), 3106-3107
-- (post-decode idle transition), 3949 (n_past_prompt advance),
-- 3953 (PROCESSING transition after prefill completes).
contract SlotLifecycle {
    invoke: (slot: Slot) -> Slot

    @invariant InitialStateIdleNone
        -- A freshly-constructed Slot starts at
        -- (state, command, released) = (idle, none, false).

    @invariant LoadPromptOnTaskArrival
        -- When the server assigns an incoming task to a Slot
        -- (server-context.cpp:1714), the Slot transitions from
        -- (idle, none) to (idle, load_prompt). State stays idle
        -- until the prefill completes; command carries the
        -- "work pending" signal.

    @invariant LoadPromptCarriesAcrossTicksUnderChunking
        -- Under Tier 4, a Slot may persist at
        -- (idle, load_prompt) across many Ticks while its
        -- prefill is admitted in chunks. The transition to
        -- PROCESSING fires only when
        -- n_past_prompt = n_prompt_tokens, which may take
        -- ceil(n_prompt_tokens / per_tick_prefill_budget)
        -- Ticks. During this carry, the slot is eligible for
        -- selection by ChunkedPrefillAdmission each Tick.

    @invariant ProcessingOnPrefillComplete
        -- When the admission loop has contributed the final
        -- chunk of the Slot's prompt (n_past_prompt reaches
        -- n_prompt_tokens), the Slot transitions to
        -- (state=processing, command=none).
        -- n_prompt_tokens_processed reaches n_prompt_tokens at
        -- this point.

    @invariant IdleOnRelease
        -- When the Slot releases (server-context.cpp:578-582),
        -- it returns to (idle, none, released=true) and is
        -- eligible for reassignment.

    @invariant ReleasedFlagSetByReleasePathOnly
        -- The `released` field becomes true only via the explicit
        -- release path; it is never set by the admission loop.
        -- The flag carries one-Tick visibility to the HTTP
        -- layer that the Slot just finished a task.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Invariants — system-wide
-- ============================================================

-- A per-token consistency rule: a BatchToken is exactly one of
-- prefill or decode (or neither, in some degenerate cases the
-- spec does not constrain — e.g. ubatch padding tokens with no
-- slot binding). The flags are not both true on the same token.
invariant PerTokenFlagExclusivity {
    for t in BatchTokens:
        not (t.is_prefill and t.is_decode)
}

-- Redefined for Tier 4: every Batch satisfies the conjunction
-- of the admission contracts. Downstream specs (in particular
-- mtp_fused_draft.allium and unified_stream_dispatch.allium)
-- reference this name as the load-bearing "the batch is shaped
-- correctly" predicate; the body is now the chunked-prefill
-- admission shape rather than the pre-Tier-4 pure-prefill OR
-- pure-decode disjunction.
invariant BatchCompositionInvariant {
    for batch in Batches:
        let tokens = BatchTokensOf(batch)
        let k = batch.tick.config_prefill_chunk_budget
        tokens.count <= k
            and tokens.all(t => not (t.is_prefill and t.is_decode))
}

-- The decode-priority side of the admission policy, lifted to a
-- system-wide property: in any Batch that contains prefill
-- tokens, every PROCESSING slot whose decode-token was ready at
-- the start of the Tick contributes a decode BatchToken to the
-- same Batch (subject to budget being able to admit them all).
invariant DecodeAdmittedWhenPrefillAdmitted {
    for batch in Batches:
        let tokens = BatchTokensOf(batch)
        let tick = batch.tick
        let processing_slots = SlotsAtTickStart(tick)
            .where(s => s.state = processing)
        let prefill_count = tokens.where(t => t.is_prefill).count
        prefill_count > 0
            implies processing_slots.all(p =>
                tokens.any(t => t.is_decode and t.slot = p))
}

-- ============================================================
-- Open Questions
-- ============================================================

-- OQ-1: Production-policy K. The contracts hold for any K in
--   [1, n_ubatch]; the production value (set via
--   --prefill-chunk-budget) is policy, not spec. T4.7's perf
--   gate measures sensitivity to K; the chosen production value
--   will be recorded in MEMORY.md, not here. Spec records the
--   open question for future cross-reference.
--
-- OQ-2: Heterogeneous slot priorities. The round-robin in
--   ChunkedPrefillAdmission.RoundRobinFairness is FIFO over
--   slot.id; it does not weight by arrival time, prompt length,
--   or SLA class. If a future scheduler introduces priority,
--   either restate the fairness invariant or factor it into a
--   dedicated priority spec. Plan file references this in the
--   T4 Out-of-scope section.
--
-- OQ-3: DFlash composition under chunked admission. T4.6's
--   GP4.l hard-binds DFlash composition (multi-slot,
--   batch-vs-serial byte-identical, closure tests, NP-invariance).
--   If a DFlash-specific carve-out is needed (e.g., the verify
--   ubatch must stay pure-decode because the DFlash kernel
--   assumes no mid-prefill rows), surface as a new contract here
--   and constrain the admission loop accordingly. Empirically
--   open until T4.6 binds.
--
-- OQ-4: MTP fused × T4. The MTP-fused decode path runs N decode
--   tokens per slot per Tick (the draft-then-verify cycle). The
--   admission loop must treat MTP fused slots as contributing
--   multiple decode BatchTokens per Tick, not one. Verify the
--   per-PROCESSING-slot decode count in DecodePriorityAdmission
--   is interpreted as "all of this slot's decode tokens for this
--   Tick" rather than "one per slot" once T4.4 wiring lands.
--   Resolves at T4.6 via the existing MTP-fused composition
--   tests.

-- ============================================================
-- Implementation notes
-- ============================================================

-- Code-side anchors (paths from yarn-agentic root, current as
-- of T3.8 close 2026-05-22; T4 will move some of these):
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:14-17
--     — enum slot_state.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:21-25
--     — enum slot_command.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:37-232
--     — struct server_slot, including n_prompt_tokens,
--       n_prompt_tokens_processed, n_past_prompt, n_decoded.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:1714
--     — LOAD_PROMPT assignment from incoming task.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3196-3206
--     — DecodeHoldGate body, removed in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D N3;
--       Tier 4 confirms it stays gone.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3623-3664
--     — batch_pending_prompt entry + the
--       active_pp_slot_id PrefillSerialisationGate; removed in
--       T4.4 and replaced by the admission scaffold.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3949
--     — n_past_prompt advance per admitted chunk (load-bearing
--       for ChunkedPrefillAdmission carry).
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:5078-5173
--     — update_slots tick sequence.
--
-- Black-box helpers used inline in the invariants above (not in
-- `deferred` per project convention — they have no separate
-- .allium spec):
--   BatchTokensOf, SlotsAtTickStart, Batches, BatchTokens.
--   batch.tick.config_prefill_chunk_budget is the per-Tick
--   snapshot of the server's K config (unchanged within a Tick).
--
-- Test infrastructure to drive from this spec:
--   - tests/spec/test-chunked-prefill-admission.cpp (T4.1):
--     synthetic 8-slot mixed-state Batch; assert all four
--     invariants hold; per-slot output byte-identical to a
--     serial-admission baseline.
--   - scripts/validate-batch-composition-trace.py (T4.0.c):
--     NDJSON trace validator; replaces the pre-Tier-4
--     MixedBatchProhibition / AtMostOnePrefillSlotPerBatch
--     checks with TokenBudgetRespected /
--     DecodePriorityAdmission / PrefillCarryProgresses.
--   - specs/multislot/BatchComposition.tla (T4.0.b): TLA+ model
--     with DecodeHoldGateOn = FALSE (Tier 4 mode).

-- ============================================================
-- Related specs
-- ============================================================

-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium
--   The Tier 3 closure. Owns the structural Bug C absence
--   property (BugCAbsenceUnderUnifiedDispatch,
--   PreservesBugCAbsence). THIS spec delegates Bug C closure
--   to that one; the admission contracts here only govern
--   WHICH tokens are in the Batch, not the mul_mat shape they
--   produce (which is uniform per Tick regardless).
--
-- mtp_fused_draft.allium
--   Covers ONE draft round's KV writes and DraftToken
--   production. The
--   FusedDraftRoundsRunOnPureDecodeBatches local invariant in
--   that spec asserts the draft KERNEL still runs on a
--   decode-shaped sub-batch (it cannot consume prefill rows).
--   Composition: a PROCESSING slot in speculative mode
--   contributes is_decode BatchTokens via the
--   DecodePriorityAdmission contract here; the kernel-side
--   draft round consumes them via the FusedDraftStep
--   contract there.
--
-- mtp_ubatch_hook.allium
--   Covers per-ubatch MTP-KV updates during the verify
--   forward. Operates downstream of llama_decode; the batch
--   shape THIS spec governs determines the ubatch shape that
--   one sees.
--
-- qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium
--   Covers the engine's per-block dispatch when one Batch
--   contains multiple seq_ids (CONTIGUOUS_BLOCKS pattern).
--   With T4's chunked-prefill admission, a Batch can be a
--   mix of seq_ids spanning both PROCESSING and LOAD_PROMPT
--   slots. qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium then governs how
--   the engine splits the batch by seq_id for the per-block
--   linear-attn dispatch.
--
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium
--   The 4D per-stream KV layout that made the
--   pre-Tier-4 DecodeHoldGate redundant by closing Bug C
--   structurally. T4 builds on that closure.
